      <category>Publication</category>
      <description>Today, the Treasurer announced the implementation of a 'standard' set of tax-related conditions that will apply to foreign investment clearances. This announcement is significant from a foreign direct investment perspective as it likely requires additional or more detailed upfront tax structuring advice prior to submission of a FIRB application, as well as a higher level of engagement with the ATO on FIRB applications.</description>
